OL,5, A clear majority of Britons agree      
OL,6, household chores should be shared - but
OL,7, women generally do them, an annual     
OL,8, survey of public views suggests.       
OL,10,FMore than three-quarters of respondents
OL,11,Fto the British Social Attitudes Survey 
OL,12,Fsaid domestic labour should be split.  
OL,14,FYet two-thirds said women do more than 
OL,15,Ftheir fair share of washing and        
OL,16,Fironing. And most said women still do  
OL,17,Fmost of the cleaning and cooking.      
OL,19,FBut ideas on gender roles have changed 
OL,20,Fconsiderably since the mid-1980s.      
